reviews.review: Really like it, probably the best one of the new trilogy

This was the movie with certain moments and storyline needed after The Last Jedi, it's a nice ending of the new trilogy and felt like being on a rollercoaster in the cinema. I enjoyed every second of that and I felt complete afterwards! 
If this isn't how SW fans wanted it, how did they then?
I understand that this movie will split fans, some will enjoy it, some won't
But overall I'm happy with this movie and I was hoping for that after TLJ

This is not a good movie. Rian Johnson and Abrams had no agreement or plan for this trilogy's story, whith this movie being living proof of it. JJ's main goal with this movie was just to retcon the horrible film that came before. The few genuinely good moments are far too spread, and ironically have nothing to do with the Skywalker family or the contrived "main plot" about the Force. Adam Driver is reduced to an errand boy with very little agency excluding one single moment near the end of the film. There's no creativity or soul. The best part about seeing this film, is that now that I know how this mess of a trilogy ended, I no longer have to ever watch these three films ever again. Go watch the film with family and friends. You may get a couple laughs at how silly some moments in the film are.

This movie was a terrible waste of time and potential.  It could have been so epic, but instead we're once again treated to paper-thin characters, awful dialogue and overblown special effects.  I hope that someday Star Wars will return to it's past glory, but Rise of Skywalker is not the movie to do it.  I'm almost out of patience with the Star Wars franchise.

Critics hate it because of the fan service and the jumbled mess that is the first 40 minutes. But if you can watch this movie and not get hit with the feels you are crazy. I felt truly satisfied throughout. Sure there were some parts that were a little out there. As a film itself, I would probably agree with critics. But as the final star wars film in the Skywalker saga? It's absolutely awesome!
Really good film, best in the sequel trilogy and top three in the saga. Loved it! Never lagged during the film.
Loved the twists and turns and the old familiar faces.
The movie did what I wanted to see.
